{
  "texts": [
    "This disparity highlights the impracticality of incorporating all available chart data into generic MLLMs' training data.",
    "Furthermore, To this end, we opt to design a data engine for a dataset of appropriate size while encompassing the real-world spectrum of chart features and QA tasks.",
    "The data engine consists of two modules: data filtering (Sect. 5.1) for efficiently utilizing the existing data and also appropriate training cost; and data generation (Sect.",
    "5.2) for optimizing the data distribution.",
    "Finally, we present the obtained visualizationreferenced dataset and benchmark (Sect. 5.3)."
  ]
}